<HEADLINE>
Chinese shares slightly lower in morning trade
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese share prices were slightly lower in Friday morning trade
despite sentiment receiving a boost from strong earnings
forecasts by banks, dealers said.Banks turned sharply higher
after Industrial and Commercial Bank of China and Shanghai Pudong
Development Bank projected favourable first-half earnings.
</P>
<P>
ICBC, the country's largest bank, said its first-half net profit
was expected to rise by more than 50 percent year-on-year.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Pudong Development Bank projected first-half profit
growth of more than 140 percent.
</P>
<P>
But oil refiners remained weak on rising fuel costs after oil
prices settled at a record 145.29 dollars per barrel overnight.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Shanghai Composite Index, which covers A and B
shares, was 18.22 points, or 0.67 percent lower at 2,685.31 at
11:00 am (0300 GMT).
</P>
